 "method": {
  "binomial_construction": "binom_prime(N,m): exact C(N,m) built as a product of prime powers p^e, e = v_p(N!) - v_p(m!) - v_p((N-m)!) via Legendre's formula (vp_factorial), for every prime p<=N (Kummer/Legendre exact method, no math.comb, no floats). Reimplemented independently in the generator for this certificate (attribution above); binom_table reuses one binom_prime call per scale group plus O(1) exact ratio updates for adjacent m, exactly as the source script does.",
  "bit_bracket": "bit_bracket(num,den): integers (L,U=L+1) with 2^L <= num/den < 2^U, found by bit_length-seeded search and VERIFIED by exact integer comparison (num >= den*2^j, or equivalently num<<(-j) >= den for negative j) -- no floats in the verdict. Applied to the LHS/RHS of each checked inequality at m (must be > 0, i.e. unsafe fires) and at m+1 (must be <= 0, i.e. construction stops firing) as the 'orientation margin'.",
  "note_on_integer_sizes": "C(N,m) itself is NOT recorded (it runs to ~2 million bits for the c=1 rows: n*H2(m/n) with n=2^21, m/n~0.532 gives ~2.09M bits). Only bit_length()s of the composite LHS/RHS products and the resulting small (tens-of-bits) orientation-margin brackets are recorded, per task instruction."
